September 10th, 2020 Update

School Meals

Recent announcements by the USDA and the Ohio Department of Education will allow us to re-start the free meal program at New Lebanon Schools similar to the program hosted by the school earlier this year. Beginning on Monday, Sept 14th, all students will be eligible to receive free lunch and breakfast each day. The program is authorized through December 31st, 2020 but may end earlier if funds are depleted before that date.

Free meals (breakfast and lunch) will be available for students while they are at school and will also be available to be taken home for students’ remote learning days in the hybrid program and for those students on full-remote…

post_text:
We are busy planning for the start of the 20/21 school year. Although state health guidelines are still undefined, we are hopeful that we will be able to return to a full daily and weekly schedule for all students. We will have enhanced cleaning and health protocols in place to minimize the spread of infection.

We are also making improvements to our online learning processes. The feedback we received from the parent survey was very helpful. It appears that we may need to have online opportunities available under some circumstances for students next year and we will strive to support students and parents with the best instruction possible.

We will provide more information as guidelines…

Dixie Middle School Says Farewell to Mrs. Staley

Dixie Middle School staff and students are bidding school counselor, Elizabeth Staley, a fond farewell at the end of the 19/20 school year. Mrs. Staley has served as the Dixie Middle School counselor since 2006 and has supported thousands of students along the way. She was instrumental in guiding many students and families toward earning four-year scholarships through the Montgomery County College Promise program.

In addition to attending to the myriad of student needs that arise over each school year, Mrs. Staley supported students in a number of activities like Girls on the Run and the 8/5 Service Club. Mrs. Staley seized every…

post_text:
Kindness “Rocks”

Mrs. Nugent, Dixie Middle School 8th Grade science teacher, very rarely gives extra credit assignments. With students just finishing a unit on plate tectonics, trying to figure out “Stay at Home” learning, and spending a lot of time on the computer, she knew it was time for something different. She created an opportunity for students to spread kindness to their community while getting outside and earning some extra credit along the way.

Most Fridays are Fellowship Fridays in Ms. Nugent’s class. The day starts with an inspirational video followed by class discussion. A Facebook post for Northeast Ohio Rocks gave me the idea for a perfect activity for 8th graders and the…

Sometimes during a year, the book of the month arrives when students aren’t in school. Most years, it isn’t a problem as books can be given to students when they return from break. When students weren’t scheduled to come back to school until May 4th at the earliest, many Dixie Elementary teachers took to the road to deliver the books so students wouldn’t need to wait.
Mrs. Amanda Ruble, Dixie Elementary 3rd Grade teachers, is one of those teachers who helped out the Easter Bunny by delivering an Easter treat a little bit early. A number of New Lebanon community members including board of education members, former students, family members, parents of former students, and even retired Dixie… More

post_text: Several DMS students put their heads together to think of ways to help our community and their friends during these unprecedented times. They decided to do a fundraiser for the food bank that would also bring the class of 2024 closer, while they can't be together. So they DESIGNED a class T-shirt. The cost to buy is 17$. Profits will go to the food bank. It is a super soft material. It doesn't have much give so if you are an in between size - size up. To buy a shirt, EMAIL: Remmey2024@gmail.com for orders. The deadline to place the order is May 1st.
